#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:4
msgid "Invasion!"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:13
msgid "In the Northern Lands, where the Mountains of Dorth reached the coast, was a bay with a narrow mouth. In this bay was the merman city of Johtha. Many bands of orcs wanted the bay for their own, so raiding parties attacked often. Usually, the orcs could be easily defeated when they entered the water, but they were still a nuisance."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:17
msgid "In 626 YW, one large raiding party was held off by king Kai Laudiss and his troops, but several merman warriors were killed in the battle. When the raiders retreated, Kai Laudiss followed them, determined to send a message by killing every last one. The raiders fled north towards Tirigaz, and the Kai caught up with them at the port city. Now, he and his warriors were severely outnumbered."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:21
msgid "The king's army fought valiantly, and killed five orcs for every soldier they lost. It was a battle the orcs would not soon forget, but the cost was high. Kai Laudiss was killed along with most of his soldiers. When the remaining soldiers returned, they told Krellis, the Kai's son, that he was now king."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:25
msgid "Kai Krellis was only a child, so he needed help to rule intelligently. Mermen rule without official advisors, but Krellis relied on the wisdom of a priestess named Cylanna. She had been a friend of his father, and he had known her as long as he could remember."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:29
msgid "With the orcs unlikely to trouble them soon, Cylanna believed that Krellis would be able to lead a more peaceful life than his father. Unfortunately, that was not to be. A new enemy appeared from under the mountains."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Dark Sorcerer, description=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:51
msgid "Undead Forces"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:121
msgid "Defeat Enemy Leader"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:161
msgid "Is something wrong priestess?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:166
msgid "Maybe. I feel death and decay."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:225
msgid "Back you fiend! You have not won yet...I will return to finish this."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:255
msgid "Kai! We are under attack! Some creatures entered our village and began slaying our citizens. I barely got out alive myself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:260
msgid "What kind of creatures?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:265
msgid "I don't rightly know. They were like men, but...but they had no skin. Our spears went right through them, and they just laughed at us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:270
msgid "Undead. This will be your first real test as a leader, Kai Krellis. You must defeat these creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:275
msgid "You should lead us personally so you can get some battle experience."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:280
msgid "I agree. I will protect you as much as I can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:285
msgid "You have few trained fighters, so you will not be able to recruit more than three of each level 1 unit. There is no limit on citizens."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:325
msgid "Rise, my slaves! We will create an army for Lord Ravanal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:334
msgid "He is raising our dead to fight against us! Even though they were your own citizens, Krellis, show no mercy. Destroy them if you can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: description=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:350
msgid "Foolish fish-men. You can't kill me that easily."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/01_Invasion.cfg:355
msgid "The merfolk saw a shadowy shape rise from the dead body of the necromancer and disappear under the mountain."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:4
msgid "Flight"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:12
msgid "Kai Krellis was concerned that the undead might return, so he decided to learn as much as possible about them. The necromancer had mentioned a 'Lord Ravanal', so that seemed like a good place to start. He sent messengers north and south along the coast to see if they could find out about Ravanal. The news he heard was not good."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:16
msgid "Mal-Ravanal was a wizard from the east who had turned himself into a lich. He had attacked the edges of Wesnoth, and was building a fearsome army of undead humans there. He had also sent necromancers to attack the orcs, and even the elves, in a quest for undead soldiers of different races. It seemed that he also wanted merfolk. There was little doubt that Kai Krellis' people would be attacked again."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:20
msgid "As the weeks went by, the veterans of the last battle helped train new recruits. Krellis' army did not yet match his father's, but he now had many competent soldiers. As he had expected, their adversaries soon returned."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:58
msgid "Move Kai Krellis to the north-west corner of the map. He must be level one or higher."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:62
msgid "Defeat the enemy leaders (Good luck.)"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Lich, description=Mal Kevek
#. [side]: type=Necromancer, description=Mel Daveth
#. [side]: type=Death Knight, description=Dead Knight
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:127 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:163 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:195 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:72 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:104 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:136
msgid "Mal-Ravanal's Forces"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:192
msgid "You may have ended my first life, but you have only made me more powerful. Now I will teach you a lesson!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mel Daveth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:197
msgid "Leave some of them for me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dead Knight
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:370 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:202
msgid "Uhhh."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mel Daveth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:207
msgid "And him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:212
msgid "We are surrounded. Look how many there are! How can we defeat them this time?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:217
msgid "I'm afraid we cannot. We need help. My old instructor, Tyegëa, teaches on an island to the North. She and her priestesses are powerful. With their help we could probably defeat these enemies. We just have to convince her to leave her enclave."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:222
msgid "You can do that, right?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:227
msgid "I do not believe I can. However, you could."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:232
msgid "Me? I've never even met Tyegëa. How can I convince her to help us if you cannot?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:237
msgid "You will just have to trust me on this. She will listen to you. I will say no more on the matter."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:242
msgid "Very well. How do we get there?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:247
msgid "We follow the coast north, then go west to Bilheld Island. Tyegëa lives on a small island to the west of Bilheld."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:252
msgid "That will take many days. I cannot leave my people here to be slaughtered by undead monsters while we go for help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:257
msgid "Of course not. They will all have to come with us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:285
msgid "We are not all soldiers used to obeying orders. I am afraid that not everyone will follow you on so strange an adventure. First you must prove you are not afraid of danger. If you leave now, many will think you are simply running away to save yourself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:291
msgid "However, I am afraid that not everyone will follow you on so strange an adventure. First you must prove you are not afraid of danger. If you leave now, many will think you are simply running away to save yourself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:298
msgid "My people will see me fight the undead before we leave, even if beating them all is impossible."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:304
msgid "But will everyone follow me on so strange an adventure? Maybe they will not trust me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:313
msgid "I believe the people will follow you. Since you have already proven your courage in battle, they will understand that you would not leave if there was any other choice."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:319
msgid "I believe they will follow you. Since you have already proven your courage in battle, they will understand that you would not leave if there were any other choice."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:404 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:339
msgid "This is impossible!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:392 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:416 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:433
msgid "I hate to leave our home, but we will return."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/02_Flight.cfg:429
msgid "Killing these enemies was good, but more will be coming. We still need to leave."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Coast"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:11
msgid "Distrustful of the open ocean, Kai Krellis lead his people up the coast."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:15
msgid "They had only just begun when they ran into wolves who had gotten wind of the battle. Some of the wolves were ridden by goblins. Orcs might have decided not to bother the merfolk, but goblins are not known for their caution."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:59
msgid "Defeat the wolf leader"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Gashnok, type=Goblin Knight, type=Goblin Knight, type=Direwolf Rider, type=Direwolf Rider
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:69
msgid "Wolf Riders"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:120
msgid "Wild Wolves"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vrunt
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:153
msgid "Let's hope those wild wolves don't get to the feast before we do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gashnok
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:158
msgid "Hold on....It looks like a feast is coming our way! Fresh fish boys! Go get it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:163
msgid "Look out people!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:181
msgid "There is something sticking out of the mud here. Ah! I got it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:188
msgid "I know what that is. It's a storm trident. It is supposed to let you control the lightning."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:193
msgid "The trident is 14-2, magical, ranged, with 'fire' damage.  (It does 14 damage on each of 2 tries, with a 70% chance to hit.)"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=$unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:200
msgid "That sounds great! I'll take it."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=$unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:209
msgid "That sounds frightening. Let someone else have it."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=$unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:235
msgid "Let me have that trident. I want to control lightning!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=$unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/03_Wolf_Coast.cfg:244
msgid "I'll just leave that trident where it is."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:4
msgid "Slavers"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:12
msgid "Now, they were farther away from home than most merfolk ever went. Only Cylanna and a few soldiers had been farther."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:59
msgid "Defeat the saurian leaders"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Gilak, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Flanker, type=Saurian Flanker
#. [side]: description=Raxisz, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Flanker, type=Saurian Flanker
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:69 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:111
msgid "Saurian Slavers"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Aglizix, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Ambusher, type=Saurian Flanker, type=Saurian Flanker
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:152
msgid "Saurians"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:258
msgid "Saurians. I hear they are not very friendly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Teeloa
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:284
msgid "Help! Save me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:289
msgid "Who are you? What is happening?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Teeloa
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:294
msgid "My name is Teelöa. I have been a slave to these saurians for almost two years. I saw you coming up the coast with soldiers, so I fled. They are right behind me, and if you don't protect me, they will kill me for sure."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:299
msgid "A slave!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gilak
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:304
msgid "You! Merman! You have some property of ours. Return it at once if you value your life."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:309
msgid "If you mean this merman, Teelöa, he is no longer your property. No person should be the property of another. In fact, I demand that you release all your slaves!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:314
msgid "Good for you Kai. I cannot abide slavery."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gilak
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:319
msgid "Foolish merman! You will soon wish you had minded your own affairs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:324
msgid "Hear this! All slaves rise up and be free! We will help you defeat your captors!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:509
msgid "Cheers erupted from several villages, and former slaves rushed out with whatever meager weapons they could find, or even no weapons at all. Screams and curses came from the saurian castles."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:524
msgid "There is a treasure chest here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:535
msgid "You receive 80 gold."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:559
msgid "That must be a drake. I am told they are fearsome, but honorable, creatures. Let him out of the cage."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:563
msgid "Uh...If you say so."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:569
msgid "This must be a drake. I am told they are honorable creatures. I am going to let him out of the cage."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:592
msgid "What is your name?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:597
msgid "I...Keshan."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:602
msgid "How did you come to be in a cage?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:607
msgid "I kill lots little lizards. They put me in cage. They try to train. I not train good."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:612
msgid "I am sure of that! Will you fight with us, Keshan?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:617
msgid "You let Keshan kill little green lizards?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:622
msgid "All of them you want!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:627
msgid "I fight with you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:632
msgid "Don't let him go too crazy. Those saurian spears will go right through his scales."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:672
msgid "Who are you, and what are you doing in a cage?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:678
msgid "Why you in cage?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Siddry
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:685
msgid "My name is Siddry. These cursed saurians nabbed me a week ago. They put me in a cage until I agreed to work for them. That seems to be their standard procedure. They tried to take my bow too, but they had some trouble with that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:690
msgid "So you will help us defeat them?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Siddry
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:695
msgid "The way I see it, you're helping me. There is nothing I would like better than to put their slavery to an end. I can't swim, so I won't be able to come with you on your travels, but I will owe you. If there is anything I can do in the future, I will do it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:700
msgid "Well met, then, friend. I am Kai Krellis, leader of the people of Jothra."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:708
msgid "Those poor slaves are being slaughtered! They should have waited for us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/04_Slavers.cfg:713
msgid "The saurians reacted faster than I thought they would. They probably hoped to take more of them by surprise as well. I'm sure they knew what could happen though."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:4
msgid "Tirigaz"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:12
msgid "Farther up the coast was the port city of Tirigaz where Kai Laudis had so soundly beaten the orcs. Bilheld was due west from there. The merfolk felt uneasy, so they took shelter in an abandoned orcish encampment as night fell."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:73
msgid "Destroy all the undead"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:77
msgid "Destroy all the undead and defeat Marg-Tonz (Bonus)"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Marg-Tonz, type=Orcish Sovereign
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:107
msgid "Orcs"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:135
msgid "Undead"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ghost scout
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:223
msgid "Found. Them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:336
msgid "I was afraid this might happen. We tarried too long fighting the saurians, and the undead have caught up with us. The spirits may have trapped us here for the night, but in the morning we will..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:341
msgid "What's going on? What are you fish men doing here? Are we constantly to be pestered by you creatures?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:346
msgid "He's one to complain about THAT."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:351
msgid "We were just passing through."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:356
msgid "Well, finish passing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:361
msgid "Actually, we have some ghosts after us now, and we would like to shelter here for a while."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:366
msgid "Forget about it! We don't want no trouble, but get off our land! Ghosts who don't like fish are your problem."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:371
msgid "If you give us couple hours to regroup and prepare our soldiers, we will go without causing you trouble."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:376
msgid "You have one hour. After that, we are tearing down that old encampment. You stay in the water if you know what's good for you. If you set foot...or whatever...on land again, we'll cut your throats. And stay off our piers. And don't touch the ships neither!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:381
msgid "I wonder how he gets customers with manners like that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:386
msgid "One hour will work for us. It will not take all of us to defeat the undead. We can decide what to do about the orc after that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:391
msgid "You will only be able to use your keep for one turn."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:456
msgid "You're still squatting on our land! I warned you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:490
msgid "I told you to stay off our land! Now you're in for it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:524
msgid "I told not to bother the ships! Now you're in for it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#. [option]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:602 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:614
msgid "Now maybe we can head west undisturbed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:612
msgid "We have destroyed the undead."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:623
msgid "This orc leader has not learned that threatening merfolk is a bad idea. We shall defeat him before we go."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:648
msgid "It seems that orc was rich! He has a chest here with over 100 pieces of gold!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Marg-Tonz
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/05_Tirigaz.cfg:675
msgid "I hate mermen!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:4
msgid "Uncharted Islands"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:12
msgid "Now the merfolk had no choice but to travel through the open ocean which they knew was more treacherous than shallow water. After a couple days, they found some islands in their path. Cylanna only vaguly remembered them, but thought they were safe. At least it seemed like a nice place to rest."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Growloff, type=Ranger
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:61
msgid "Growloff and His Pets"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:117 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:115
msgid "Defeat enemy leader"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Cuttle Fish, description=pet
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:126
msgid "Beloved Pet"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:164
msgid "Uh oh. There is someone else here. Hey! He is being attacked by a cuttle fish!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:168
msgid "Look my pet, here's a yummy treat!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:172
msgid "Or...is he TALKING to it?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:176
msgid "It is worse than that. I think we are the treat!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:180
msgid "Who is ready for a merfolk snack?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:184
msgid "Brace yourselves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:205
msgid "Oh no! Look what he has now. And I thought the cuttle fish was bad!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:224
msgid "You killed my pet! You'll pay for that!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:250
msgid "Don't kill me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:254
msgid "But you attacked us with these monsters."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:258
msgid "They are my friends. I've been so lonely here...and you killed so many of my friends. They could be your friends too. Spare me, and I'll give you my favorite cuttle fish. His name is Inky."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:262
msgid "I do not want a dangerous animal like that!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:266
msgid "But he's tame! Really! He understands dozens of commands. He'll do what you tell him. He's a really nice fish."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:270
msgid "Maybe we could use a pet sea monster."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:274
msgid "All right. I'll take the cuttle fish. But you had better not bother us again, or I'll kill you and all the rest of your pets."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Growloff
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:278
msgid "Of course, of course. I promise! I never wanted to hurt you nice people anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Cuttle Fish, description=Inky
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:286
msgid "Inky"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/06_Uncharted_Islands.cfg:296
msgid "Right. Tell me how to control this thing."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:4
msgid "Bilheld"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:12
msgid "Finally, the merfolk arrived at Bilheld. Their destination, and help, was just behind it. The island was inhabited, however, and the residents didn't look happy to see them."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Vlagnor, type=Drake Flameheart
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:64
msgid "Drakes"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:128
msgid "What you mermans doing here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:132
msgid "We have business with Tyegëa on the other side of the island."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:136
msgid "That the mermaid witch!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:140
msgid "Witch?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:144
msgid "Witch?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:148
msgid "She kill drakes. If you her friend, we kill you. We not want more mermans blasting and poking."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:152
msgid "We are going around this island whether you want us to or not."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:156
msgid "We not. Vlagnor stop you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:167
msgid "Bhogh! Bzoghlan frraznab bzogh nagond?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:171
msgid "Nach. These my friends. I go with them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vlagnor
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/07_Bilheld.cfg:175
msgid "Bhagzhod! Then you die with them!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:4
msgid "Talking to Tyegëa"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:12
msgid "It had been more of an adventure than the Kai Krellis had planned, but they were finally at their destination. The small island where Tyegëa and her students lived was before them. Krellis was sure he would get the help he needed here. Cylanna was less sure, but kept her thoughts to herself."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: description=Tyegea, type=Mermaid Diviner
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:73 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:108
msgid "Tyegëa and Priestesses"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:104
msgid "Choose a unit to take the holy water"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:143
msgid "Krellis...be careful about what you say. Tyegëa is a bit unpredictable."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:147
msgid "Welcome merfolk! It has been a long time since outsiders have visited. And Cylanna! It is pleasant to see you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:151
msgid "The honor is ours. I present Kai Krellis of Jotha."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:155
msgid "Indeed! So this is the one. Does he know?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:159
msgid "Know what?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:163
msgid "Now is not the time. We have a desperate errand, Tyegëa. Jotha is under attack."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:167
msgid "We were forced to flee for our lives from legions of undead. If you help us, we can remove these spirits from our home."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:171
msgid "And what makes you think I want to leave my comfortable home and risk death by attacking armies of undead?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:175
msgid "I guess I had hoped..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:179
msgid "I am sure it was Cylanna's idea that you come here. She has a reason. Don't you Cylanna? Tell him what it is."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:183
msgid "(Sigh.) I had hoped to avoid this, but I seems I cannot."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:187
msgid "I never agreed that secrecy was necessary, but I respected Maudin's wishes in the matter. However, Indress and Maudin are dead. I am not, therefore my wishes should now be respected."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:191
msgid "You knew my grandparents?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:195
msgid "Kai Maudin is your father's father, Krellis, but his wife, Indress, was not his mother. She raised your father, and you called her grandmother, but Tyegëa is your father's mother."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:199
msgid "What?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:203
msgid "I am your grandmother."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:207
msgid "Before Maudin was Kai, he went on an adventure of his own."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:211
msgid "I am astonished. I suppose I should be honored to have such a distinguished ancestor. Now I understand why Cylanna knew you would help us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:215
msgid "That remains to be seen. I find it disturbing that a Kai, and my descendant would be here begging for help. Before I agree to save you, you have to prove that my blood flows in your veins. Prove that your are, despite appearences, courageous, and worthy of my help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:219
msgid "Well, I defeated the Drakes on your island."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:223
msgid "Bah! Drakes only look dangerous. Soldiers carrying spears make short work of them. No, I have something else in mind. You will retrieve the Flaming Sword of Agnovon from the Swamp of Desolation. South of the swamp, near a ruined castle, lives a mage named Caladon. He has lusted after the sword for years, so he will know where to find the lich who has it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:227
msgid "A lich has it? We were fleeing liches in the first place."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:231
msgid "There is only one of them. If you cannot defeat even one lich, you must be expecting me to get rid of all of your undead myself!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:235
msgid "My apologies. You are right of course. We will complete this task."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:239
msgid "I will not send you away completely empty-handed though. I can spare some holy water for one of your soldiers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:250
msgid "The holy water will make melee attacks do 'arcane' damage for the rest of the campaign. Choose a unit to take it. You may recruit or recall a unit if you want."
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:262
msgid "Holy Water"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/08_Talking_To_Tyegea.cfg:280
msgid "Now go. Come back with the flaming sword, and my priestesses and I will help you save Jotha."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "The Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:12
msgid "The party traveled back to the mainland and followed the shore north. Kai Krellis had much to think about. First, he was reevaluating the way he saw his family. Second, he was nervous about the task ahead. After all their experience he was sure they could handle it, but he was afraid he would lose some good soldiers. He was in turns angry at Tyegëa for sending him on this extra journey, and grateful that she was willing to help him retake his city."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:16
msgid "After several days, the smell of the swamp was just becoming noticeable when they came across a small ruined castle like Tyegëa had mentioned. Night was falling, and it was very dark beneath the trees, but Krellis was in a hurry now that the end of their journey was in sight. He decided to go ashore and try to find the mage immediately."
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:92
msgid "Hungry Creatures"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:111
msgid "Find Caladon the mage"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:226
msgid "I do not much care for the look of this area."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Teeloa
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:230
msgid "I just heard a splash. I think something's out there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:234
msgid "Let us find the mage quickly and leave."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:373
msgid "Hey, that cave is full of bats! Here they come."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:377
msgid "I hope there aren't any more in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:383
msgid "Little hungry bats kind of cute."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:387
msgid "Except that they are hungry for us! I hope there aren't any more in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:466
msgid "Hey, I found somebody!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Keshan
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:472
msgid "There somebody here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:476
msgid "Whoa there! BACK off or else!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:480
msgid "Do not worry about him. He is friendly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:486
msgid "You must be Caladon. We are glad to see you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:490
msgid "I am Caladon. Am I glad to see YOU?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:494
msgid "I am Kai Krellis of Jotha. I am seeking a flaming sword, and I am told you know where to find it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:498
msgid "Ha! A MERman wants the Flaming Sword of AGNOVON! Why would YOU be able to get it when so many others could NOT? Although you do have an impressive collection of friends there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:502
msgid "Whether I can succeed or not, I must try. Will you help me find it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:506
msgid "I will show you EXACTLY where it is, but knowing where to FIND it isn't the hard part. Oh, no! You will see, my fine merman, you will see."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:510
msgid "We would be very happy if you would guide us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:514
msgid "I would be HAPPY to guide such a pretty mermaid AND her friends. Follow me everybody!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:528 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1021 ./Dead_Water/utils/dw-utils.cfg:142
msgid "Cylanna! I need you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:532 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1025
msgid "Tyegëa will never forgive me. We are lost."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/09_The_Mage.cfg:546 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1039 ./Dead_Water/utils/dw-utils.cfg:156
msgid "We are lost without our leader!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:6
msgid "The Flaming Sword"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:14
msgid "Caladon lead them just a little way up the shore. They were still on the outskirts of the swamp, and despite its name, the swamp wasn't that desolate here. Many hardy people were scraping a living out of the damp soil."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:209 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:630
msgid "Pry the flaming sword from the dead hand of its owner"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:281 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:213 ./Dead_Water/utils/dw-utils.cfg:121
msgid "Death of Kai Krellis"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:217 ./Dead_Water/utils/dw-utils.cfg:125
msgid "Death of Cylanna"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:221
msgid "Death of Caladon"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:225 ./Dead_Water/utils/dw-utils.cfg:129
msgid "Run out of Turns"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$spy_unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:271
msgid "(whispered) Kai, I heard Caladon muttering about the sword. I think he may try to take it for himself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:275
msgid "(whispered) Thank you $spy_unit.user_description|. I will keep that in mind, but it may be hard for us to stop him with that teleporting trick he has."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:280
msgid "Here we are. See that castle in the distance? That's where Agnovon has the sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:284
msgid "The lich is Agnovon?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:288
msgid "Well, he calls himself Mal Govon now, but yes. He called this land the KINGDOM of Agnovon. He was its first king. And its last, and every one in between, too! He kept getting older and older, but he never died. Well, NOW he's dead of course. He still putters around in that castle over there, but he hasn't really cared about keeping his kingdom under control for a good long while. I bet I can wake him up, though. Watch THIS!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:292
msgid "All the merfolk clamped their hands over their ears as Caladon's strident voice got much louder than any of them would have believed to be possible."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:297
msgid "AGNOVON, I'VE COME FOR YOUR SWORD! TODAY YOU WILL REMEMBER FEAR! Heh heh."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:311
msgid "A voice came back like wind moaning through dry leaves. Though it was only whispered, they all heard it better than they wanted."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Govon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:316
msgid "What I remember, you old fool, is you leaving behind the smouldering bodies of the orcs you had brought to try to take my sword. Now, you bring mermen. When they lay expiring like gasping fish on the shore, will you not flee again? Do not speak to me of fear."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:320
msgid "We are here of our own accord, and we will take that sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Govon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:324
msgid "The merman speaks. Tell it to go away, Caladon, if it doesn't want to get hurt."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:328
msgid "That does it. Attack!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:341
msgid "A word of warning, young Kai. I carry a Staff of RIGHTEOUS Flame. If you let me die, I will take YOU all with me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Howyrth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:372
msgid "Hello there! Who are you? Were you the ones shouting about taking a sword?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:377
msgid "I am Kai Krellis of Jotha. I am attempting to defeat Mal Govon and take his sword. Would you like to join us in battle against a common enemy?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Howyrth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:382
msgid "I don't know if that creature is really our enemy. He has never bothered us, and I have to stay here and guard the area anyway. However, I'm sure many townsfolk would be happy of the extra income if you want to hire them to help you fight. I guess we would be happy to get rid of the monster just in case."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:386
msgid "You can now recruit human villagers, but you will not be able to recall them in future scenarios."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Siddry
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:433
msgid "Kai Krellis! What are you doing here? I thought you were travelling south when I met you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:437
msgid "Friend Siddry!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Howyrth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:441
msgid "You know each other?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Siddry
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:445
msgid "Kai Krellis is the one who saved me from slavery, Howyrth. I told him I would repay him if I could, and here is my chance. My friends and I will join you in your fight, Kai Krellis. We are yours to command until you have your sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:572
msgid "Now we have the sword!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:577
msgid "Correction. Now I have the sword!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:657
msgid "It's MINE! The Flaming Sword of Agnovon IS ALL MINE! I can feel warmth SPREADING through me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:682
msgid "What? We won that sword!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:687
msgid "Well, it's true that you helped, so I won't kill you. But I don't trust you, so leave my realm. Go on. I will grant you some time. The benevolence of Caladon will be LEGENDARY! Heh heh, HA!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$staff_tip_off
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:692
msgid "(whispered) Kai! He dropped his righteous flame staff! We can attack him now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:724
msgid "You DARE attack ME! You will regret that. Witness the POWER of the Flaming Sword of Caladon! I call on the ELEMENT OF FIRE to DO MY BIDDING!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:791
msgid "You aren't leaving yet. My patience is at an END! Witness the POWER of the Flaming Sword of Caladon! I call on the ELEMENT OF FIRE to DO MY BIDDING!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:871
msgid "Now we can finally grab that sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:887
msgid "I am not going with you. One of you should take the sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:908
msgid "This sword is 8-4, magical, with 'fire' damage.  (It does 8 damage on each of 4 swings, with a 70% chance to hit.)"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:915 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:956
msgid "I'll carry this sword, but I don't know how to summon fire demons."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=unit
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:924 ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:965
msgid "This sword is not right for me. Let someone else have it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:996
msgid "We thank all you humans for your help, and release you from any farther obligations. Where we are going, you cannot easily follow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1072
msgid "Aghh! Die!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1077
msgid "He has that staff of..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Caladon
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1089
msgid "CURSE you mermen!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$spy_unit.description
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/10_The_Flaming_Sword.cfg:1094
msgid "What a lunatic!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:4
msgid "Getting Help"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:12
msgid "Kai Krellis no longer feared the open ocean, and made straight for Tyegëa's island to show her the flaming sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:174
msgid "We have brought the Flaming Sword. Caladon tried to steal it for himself, but we were able to get it back from him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:178
msgid "He did not part with it willingly, so he must be dead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:182
msgid "It is as you say."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:186
msgid "No matter. He was a fool. Now, you have done as I asked grandson, so I will travel with you to your home and help you rid it of restless spirits. My priestesses will come also, and will be at your disposal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/11_Getting_Help.cfg:242
msgid "You may now recruit mermaid priestesses!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:4
msgid "Revenge"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:12
msgid "The mission had been more difficult than Kai Krellis would have believed when he started. Finally though, the end was in sight. He had seen how priestesses could carve through masses of undead, and now he traveled with a whole contingent of them. Tyegëa was even more powerful, though a little unpredictable."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:15
msgid "Krellis had also fought along side many soldiers over the weeks, and some of them were quite powerful in their own right. They were all tired from their journey, but as they neared home, their weariness fell from them."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:18
msgid "The mermen arrived during the night, and silently glided to the castle in the middle of the bay. Their faces were grim as they surveyed the ransacked homes and fouled waters. Mal-Ravanal was to blame, and they would make him pay this day."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:277
msgid "Defeat all the enemy leaders"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:344
msgid "At dawn, the mermen took a look at their opponents."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:350
msgid "This doesn't look too bad."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:355
msgid "Maybe not yet, but just wait."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mel Daveth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:360
msgid "The mermen...they came back! Bring back the search parties! Call back the hordes!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kevek
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:365
msgid "Just make some more, you fool. There are plenty of corpses to go around."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:378
msgid "I suppose this DOES look a little overwhelming. I may enjoy it though. It can be satisfying to rain holy fire down on misbehaving spirits."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwabbo
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:383
msgid "Absolutely! Bring 'em on!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tyegea
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:390
msgid "I was wrong. You are no grandson of MINE!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:397
msgid "I have failed my people."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dead Knight
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:411
msgid "Gruh!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mel Daveth
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:418
msgid "Save me Lord Ravanal!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:429
msgid "That one had a way with words."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:437
msgid "We have retaken our home!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kai Krellis
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:448
msgid "Cylanna! I will miss you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cylanna
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/12_Revenge.cfg:459
msgid "Tyegëa! No!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:4
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:32
msgid "After destroying Mal-Ravanal's henchmen, Kai Krellis waited nervously for another attack. But, it never came. Krellis sent some messengers south to find out what they could. The news that came back was better than good. Mal-Ravanal was dead! Soldiers of Wesnoth had defeated him at about the same time the mermen had defeated the undead at Jotha. With the evil wizard gone, the mermen relaxed and began rebuilding in earnest, and soon Jotha was restored."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:38
msgid "Not everything was normal, of course. Many good merfolk had been lost in the first attacks and on the journey. The visiting priestesses did much to console the families of the dead, and as it always does, life continued. In a few months, the giggles of children could be heard echoing through shallows. Many of those children were named after Kai Krellis, Gwabbo, Cylanna, and the other heroes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:49
msgid "Tyegëa returned to her home, but continued to keep in touch with her grandson. Most of her priestesses went with her, but a few of them stayed in Jotha, enriching the culture of the city."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:62
msgid "Cylanna never traveled far again. She stayed in Jotha as a respected elder. Krellis didn't need advising any more, so her main work was healing the sick, and presiding at christenings and weddings. All this agreed with her disposition much better than battling undead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:69
msgid "Kai Krellis was somber over the next months as he grieved over the loss of Cylanna, but the grief diminished with time leaving only fond memories."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:82
msgid "Gwabbo lived to a ripe old age in Jotha. Tales of his heroics were told to merfolk children for generations thereafter. He became an almost legendary figure."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:95
msgid "Teeloa returned to his home where he had been captured by the saurians. He was delighted to find that many of his family members had also returned. He visited Jotha frequently, and remained friends with all the other veterans."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:108
msgid "Keshan returned to Bilheld where the drakes were still leaderless. He beat them all into submission (which is the drake way) and ruled there with an iron fist."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:121
msgid "Inky lived with Krellis at court and frolicked in the kelp beds of Jotha until he became fat and lazy in his old age."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: ./Dead_Water/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:129
msgid "Kai Krellis had many adventures during his life, but none of them ever compared to the fantastic mission of his youth."
msgstr ""

